<br>
I know there are several Fiery Defenders on this server.  How did you guys do Miragul? <p>Phread
The Old Man of Torvus Vir</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uhothrog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hothrog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/27/01 8:23:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Lich of Miragul and the Fiery Avenger</span><hr size=1> As far as I know he doesn't despawn till ya kill him, He was up for longer then two hours when VE killed him for my FA recently. If he is then we got extremely luck but I'm pretty sure it took more then 2 hours to get the guild to Everfrost and he remained up during that time. Try watching him for 2 hours to see if he despawns?<br>
<br>
---Hothrog, 55 Paladin of Brell, Valiant Elite <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ubaldricsuzushii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baldric Suzushii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/27/01 10:03:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Lich of Miragul and the Fiery Avenger</span><hr size=1> We did him 2 times within 2 weeks and we killed him within 3 hours of server re-pop. If time is an issue for you then plan around the next patch.  Have your groups camp near EF or be prepared for the fight as soon as the severs come up.<br>
<br>
I haven't heard of the despawning and it needs to be reported unless it's a stealth change.<br>
<br>
good luck<br>
<br>
<br>
Baldric<br>
59 Knight<br>
L`Malla <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uheraklesmoltenbrau.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Herakles Moltenbrau</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/27/01 12:37:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Lich of Miragul and the Fiery Avenger</span><hr size=1> I have not heard about him despawning spontaniously.  <br>
<br>
